column1: When you hear your owner say they need to hatch another egg, but you've already been on 17 walks today. 10/10 https://t.co/lFEoGqZ4oA
column2: This is Sebastian. He's super h*ckin fluffy. That's really all you need to know. 11/10 would snug intensely https://t.co/lqr0NdtwQo
column3: This is Maximus. A little rain won't stop him. He will persevere. 12/10 innovative af  https://t.co/2OmDMAkkou
column4: Like doggo, like pupper version 2. Both 11/10 https://t.co/9IxWAXFqze
column5: This is Ralphie. He's being treated for an overactive funny bone, which is no joke. 12/10 would try to pet with a straight face https://t.co/UU3KqQF5n5
column6: This is Clark. He passed pupper training today. Round of appaws for Clark. 13/10 https://t.co/7pUjwe8X6B
column7: This is Tycho. She just had new wheels installed. About to do a zoom. 0-60 in 2.4 seconds. 13/10 inspirational as h*ck https://t.co/DKwp2ByMsL
column8: C'mon guys. Please only send in dogs. We only rate dogs, not Exceptional-Tongued Peruvian Floor Bears. Thank you... 12/10 https://t.co/z30iQLiXNo
column9: We only rate dogs. Please don't send perfectly toasted marshmallows attempting to drive. Thank you... 13/10 https://t.co/nvZyyrp0kd
column10: Oh my this spooked me up. We only rate dogs, not happy ghosts. Please send dogs only. It's a very simple premise. Thank you... 13/10 https://t.co/M5Rz0R8SIQ
column11: Meet Clifford. He's quite large. Also red. Good w kids. Somehow never steps on them. Massive poops very inconvenient. Still 14/10 would ride https://t.co/apVOyDgOju
column12: This is Sebastian. He can't see all the colors of the rainbow, but he can see that this flag makes his human happy. 13/10 #PrideMonth puppo https://t.co/XBE0evJZ6V
column13: This is Ralphus. He's powering up. Attempting maximum borkdrive. 13/10 inspirational af https://t.co/YnYAFCTTiK
